  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6560.56 sitting below the massive +33.4B gamma wall at 6580 and in PIN regime, dealers are positioned to sell any rallies toward 6580 and provide buying support above the 6550 negative gamma zone. The thick positive gamma cushion from 6565-6580 should cap upside momentum and create a mean-reverting environment, with dealers mechanically selling delta as price approaches the 6580 max gamma strike. Watch for increased volatility compression between 6565-6575 as multiple positive gamma walls create a magnetic price attraction zone, while any break below 6550 flips dealers into amplifying mode where they'd sell into weakness.",
